# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `sndr_private/` — single consolidated private maintainer tree.
#
# Everything that should not ship publicly lives under this one root:
#   sndr_private/planning/   — RU planning + audit + roadmap notes
#                              (was docs/_internal/)
#   sndr_private/internal/   — operator-specific compose + scripts
#                              (was internal/)
#   sndr_private/snapshots/  — pre-arm state captures
#                              (was snapshots/)
#   sndr_private/runs/       — bench / probe outputs
#   sndr_private/pyproject-engine.toml  — commercial-tier wheel template
#
# Single rule → easier to review, no scattered _internal / _private /
# private patterns across the tree.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
sndr_private/

# Backup / temp files (still allowed anywhere)
*.bak
*.backup-*
*.tmp

# Logs / generated result JSON (bench output, probe runs, …)
*.log
*.results.json
*.bench.json

# Genesis package-data JSON is source — keep it tracked even though the
# generic `*.json` rule above existed historically. Audit 2026-05-14
# (CURRENT_PROJECT_RECHECK_CLEANUP_ERRORS_2026-05-14_eaa44975_RU.md P0-2):
# wheel / clean-clone need these artifacts; the generic `*.json` rule was
# silently dropping them.
!vllm/sndr_core/schemas/
!vllm/sndr_core/schemas/*.json
!vllm/sndr_core/manifests/
!vllm/sndr_core/manifests/*.json
!vllm/sndr_core/configs/
!vllm/sndr_core/configs/**/*.json
!schemas/
!schemas/*.json
!evidence/.gitkeep
!benchmarks/cross_rig_reports/**/*.json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `evidence/patch_proof/` — static-proof JSONs are operator-generated
# per host (carry host name + measured_at timestamp + commit SHA at
# generation time). Operators run `sndr patches prove --all` after
# clone — see `docs/INSTALL.md` and CI workflow. The directory itself
# stays tracked via the `evidence/.gitkeep` exemption above.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
evidence/patch_proof/*.json
!evidence/patch_proof/_waivers/
!evidence/patch_proof/_waivers/*.yaml

# vLLM compiled artifacts
*.so
.cache/

# Genesis-specific local state
genesis_bench_v*.md
README.md.backup-*

# Internal-only audit / plan / draft files at repo root (must live in
# `Genesis_internal_docs/` sibling dir per Sander's "internal docs outside
# project tree" rule — see feedback_internal_docs_outside_project memory).
# These patterns catch accidental drops; move violators OUT manually.
genesis_*_audit*.md
genesis_master_plan*.md
genesis_improvement_plan*.md
genesis_runtime_*.md
genesis_local_*.md
genesis_deep_*.md
genesis_project_*.md
github_research*.md
grok_*.md
todos-log-*.md
.README_*backup*.md
.README_v*_backup*.md

# ─── Commercial engine package boundary (defense-in-depth) ───────────
# `vllm/sndr_engine/` is the COMMERCIAL package namespace. It lives
# inside the `vllm/` import path (cannot be moved into sndr_private/
# without breaking Python imports), so it gets its own gitignore rule.
# Primary boundary: a real release moves sndr_engine to a SEPARATE
# private repo. This rule is the safety net against accidental
# `git add .` on a development checkout.
vllm/sndr_engine/

# Audit / plan files at repo root (also catches sndr_*_audit_*.md)
sndr_*_audit_*.md
sndr_*_plan_*.md
sndr_repeat_*.md

# Audit P1-B closure 2026-05-12: additional generated/transient artifacts.
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
# Internal research artifacts (transient bench-time analysis)
.research_marlin_moe_*.py

# Runtime bench artefacts — output of `tools/genesis_bench_suite.py`.
# Contain endpoint / model details; not for git tracking.
# Archive bench evidence belongs under `sndr_private/planning/bench_results/`.
benchmarks/runs/
